pages.name: Page 1
pages.contentHtml: The catacombs beneath Eldra’s Temple were not on any official record. Sealed long ago by the last high priest, they were said to be cursed, built over an ancient tomb older than any empire.Lost in the Catacombs The catacombs beneath Eldra’s Temple were not on any official record. pages.name: Page 2
pages.contentHtml: When the earthquakes cracked the foundations, a passage was revealed. The clergy sent down a scout. His name was Fenric.When the earthquakes cracked the foundations, a passage was revealed. The clergy sent down a scout. His name was Fenric. When the earthquakes cracked the foundations, a passage was revealed. The clergy sent down a scout. His name was Fenric. He never returned. A rescue party followed, torches blazing, but they found only their own footprints looping endlessly. He never returned. pages.name: Page 3
pages.contentHtml: The walls whispered. Candles refused to light. And something laughed from the dark. One by one, they disappeared. Journals found later described doors that led back to where they started, hallways that changed direction, and lights that blinked from behind the stones.The walls whispered. pages.name: Page 4
pages.contentHtml: One entry read, "I think the catacombs are alive." Another, written in shaky hand, simply said, "We are not alone." pages.name: Page 5
pages.contentHtml: They wear our faces, speak in our voices. I saw myself in the mirror, but it wasn't me." The temple was closed again, the entrance sealed with iron and silver runes. But every year, during the deepest night of winter, the bells toll from beneath the stone. No one goes near the temple now.
